## 📈 IX. RENDIMIENTO & ESCALABILIDAD

### 9.1 Patrones Positivos

| Patrón | Impacto |
|:-------|:--------|
| VirtualList para listas largas | 🟢 Previene DOM bloat |
| LoadingSkeleton (shimmer) | 🟢 Perceived performance |
| React.memo en componentes pesados | 🟢 Reduce re-renders |
| Zustand (no Redux) | 🟢 Minimal re-renders |
| IndexedDB cache (9 tablas) | 🟢 Offline + speed |
| Optimistic updates | 🟢 UI instantánea |

### 9.2 Riesgos de Escalabilidad

| Riesgo | Impacto | Mitigation |
|:-------|:-------:|:-----------|
| Supabase Free Tier limits | 🔴 | Upgrade a Pro ($25/mo) |
| 37 manager views en un page | 🟡 | Code splitting / lazy loading |
| No lazy routes | 🟡 | `React.lazy()` para pages |
| Bundle size sin análisis | 🟡 | Agregar bundle analyzer |
| Sin CDN para assets | 🟡 | Supabase Storage o Cloudflare |
| Realtime channels sin cleanup | 🟡 | Verificar unsubscribe en unmount |

### 9.3 Scoring Performance

| Escenario | Score | Justificación |
|:----------|:-----:|:-------------|
| 🟢 Optimista | 7.5/10 | VirtualList, Zustand, offline-first, optimistic UI |
| 🟡 Realista | 6.0/10 | Bundle no analizado, sin code splitting, sin CDN |
| 🔴 Pesimista | 4.5/10 | 37 views cargados eager + Supabase Free = timeout en áreas rurales NZ con mala conexión |

